rComments: Took it SP'14 There group projects (observation & papers), pop quizzes and exams (challenging). He doesn't put slides on compass so you need to be there and take good notes. The one HDFS class I didn't get an A in because I guess I underestimated how much I needed to study. But he's nice & will re-explain things you don't get. But: no study guides

He is honestly a very good teacher. Very nice and helpful. Make sure to attend EVERY class and listen while you take notes. If you go over the notes and READ the chapters that go with the notes, you can get an A on the exams. Projects are easy. There are not many As on the exams  . They definitely require you to study.
